Adoption Strategy (Constraint-Oriented Influence Stack aligned)

Gradient Attraction Principle (GAP)

Make Z₀ feel:
	•	smoother
	•	more controlled
	•	higher status (calm > chaotic)

⸻

Distributed Exposure Convergence (DEC)
	•	seed in speech patterns
	•	repeat in consistent cadence
	•	normalize through imitation (not enforcement)

⸻

Conductor Principle (CP)

Use Z₀ selectively:
	•	not every gap
	•	only where rhythm matters

This preserves signal quality and avoids overuse fatigue.

⸻

Canopy Protocol (Reality Check)

Z₀ is valid only if:
	•	listeners perceive speech as clearer or more composed
	•	not awkward or artificial

If not → adjust phonetic form, not principle.

⸻

Failure Modes
	•	Overuse → robotic speech
	•	Wrong tone → sounds dismissive (“eh”)
	•	Social mismatch → feels unnatural in some groups

Mitigation:
Keep Z₀ light, sparse, and adaptive.

